The paper addresses the problem of finding reliable dense correspondences between a pair of images using an end-to-end trainable convolutional neural network architecture. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of weak supervision and the application of the proposed method to a range of matching tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of the proposed method for indoor visual localization, which suggests that it may belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the state-of-the-art results on the PF Pascal dataset, which is a benchmark for image matching, suggesting that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
